Sentencas: The influence of pressure on an SOFC was studied with steam-reformed methane as a fuel.
Titulo: Pressurized Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Reformate as Fuel

Sentencas: Experiments were performed with a reformate containing 58.4% H-2, 20% H2O, 12.2% CO, 5.5% CO2 and 3.9% CH4 and another mixture containing 18% H-2, 34% H2O, 2% CO, 27% CO2 and 19% CH4 as well as a hydrogen/nitrogen mixture.
Titulo: Pressurized Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Reformate as Fuel

Sentencas: The influence of pressure on OCV, power density at constant voltage and constant current as well as on gas composition was examined for the different fuels.
Titulo: Pressurized Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Reformate as Fuel

Sentencas: Pressure dependency of OCV was found to be different for the reformate gases than for hydrogen.
Titulo: Pressurized Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Reformate as Fuel

Sentencas: The pressure increase of OCV through pressurization for reformates showed a strong dependency on temperature due to changes in the equilibrium gas compositions of the fuel.
Titulo: Pressurized Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Reformate as Fuel

Sentencas: Under load pressurization showed a positive effect on performance for all fuels.
Titulo: Pressurized Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Reformate as Fuel

Sentencas: Power density increases of up to 70% were found with reformate as fuel.
Titulo: Pressurized Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Reformate as Fuel
